N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 21 ยง 5204.1 - Definitions

State Regulations
(a) Board means the

New York State 911 Board. (b) PSAP
means public safety answering point, a site designated and operated by a local
governmental entity for the purpose of receiving emergency calls from customers
of a wireless telephone service supplier. (c) Expedited deployment funding means the

State assistance provided pursuant to this Part to local public safety
answering points for eligible wireless 911 costs. (d) Plan or plans means a priority enhanced
wireless 911 plan or plans. Notes
